[div class=p 
	"If you have a 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=published movie|href=/Movies)
	" (whether current or obsolete), you will get a Player rank. Which Player rank you get depends on your currently published movies and their rating.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"The formula for a player's score
	]em
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Each player will get a score Z, which is determined by summing player point contributions from individual movies (Z_movie):
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Rating of movie (r) is calculated as weighted average of ratings (authors' own ratings are ignored here).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Z_movie=O*max(M*r^max(2.6-0.2*average_ratings/ratings,1)/sqrt(p), 5), where p is number of players, M=1.5 for stars, M=1 for standard and alternative. O=1 if movie is current, 10^-6 otherwise. Tech/entertainment ratings count as 1 rating here. Author ratings are included in count.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=PlayerRanks 
	"Player ranks
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Your value for Z determines your Player rank:
	$LF
]div
[table 
	[tbody 
		[tr 
			[th 
				"Player rank
			]th
			[th 
				"Z
			]th
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				"Former player
			]td
			[td 
				"Z<1
			]td
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				"Player
			]td
			[td 
				"1≤Z<250
			]td
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				"Active player
			]td
			[td 
				"250≤Z<500
			]td
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				"Experienced player
			]td
			[td 
				"500≤Z<1000
			]td
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				"Skilled player
			]td
			[td 
				"1000≤Z<2000
			]td
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				"Expert player
			]td
			[td 
				"Z≥2000
			]td
		]tr
	]tbody
]table
[div class=p 
	"Note that your score for obsoleted movies is multiplied by a very small number. This way, they don't count towards your score, but they do keep your score non-zero, which means that people who had all of their movies obsoleted will get the Former player rank.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Your score is displayed after your player rank (for example, if you see "Player (146)", your score is 146 and in your forum profile.
]div
